{
  "article_id": "Woodward1931",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "ABOUT 1810, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Russian fur-hunters",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " cruised into Southern California waters seeking new hunting-grounds. The prized sea-otter then existed in great numbers in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Channel Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Thither came ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Russians",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and their imported ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Aleutian hunters",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_aleuts",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", slaughtering not only the fur-bearing animals but ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " as well.",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Tiny, fog-bound ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was the spot ",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the savage northern raiders",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " visited more often than any other.",
        "tropes": [
          11,
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Numerous clashes took rapid toll of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " who were left after "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission padres",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " had induced numbers of them to work in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mainland missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "mi_ventura",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Fernando",
        "entity_key": "mi_losangeles",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sgabriel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The lackless San Nicolenos",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1835 were reduced to "
      },
      {
        "text": "a mere handful",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission authorities",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", seeking to save the lives of these pitiful few, sent "
      },
      {
        "text": "a boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " to bring "
      },
      {
        "text": "the remnant of the tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " from "
      },
      {
        "text": "their island home",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Good landing-places are rare on any of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is one of the worst of the lot. Consequently "
      },
      {
        "text": "the rescuers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", working in a heavy sea, were under severe handicap. Despite the difficulties, they managed to get the last boatload on board, when suddenly "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "screamed!"
      }
    ]
  ]
}